                <p>Charleswood is a residential community in Calgary, Alberta's northwest quadrant. It's near Crowchild Trail and the University of Calgary on the east side. It is bordered to the north by Nose Hill Park and to the southeast by Confederation Park.</p>
                <p>The neighbourhood is situated at the foot of Nose Hill Park, one of North America's largest urban parks. Homes in Charleswood are conveniently located near the city centre, the University of Calgary, SAIT Polytechnic, and the Brentwood Mall. </p>
                <p>The majority of the properties in Charleswood were developed in the 1960s and have undergone extensive modifications. It is a well-established neighbourhood with lovely trees and parks. Dog owners in Calgary have access to a few of the nicest off-leash areas in the city.</p>
                <p>Houses in Charleswood usually include a lot of front and backyard space, as well as a modest driveway or a detached garage at the back by an alley. They're usually bungalows or tiny two-story houses with two to four bedrooms. The large yards are ideal for trampolines, swing sets, and outdoor entertaining. </p>
