        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Demographics</h3>
            <p>Charleswood, a mature and peaceful neighbourhood in northwest Calgary, was first established in 1959. </p>
            <p>The community had a population of 3,421 people living in 1,494 homes in the 2012 municipal census, up 1.9% from its 2011 census of 3,357. </p>
            <p>In 2000, the typical household income in this neighbourhood was $63,828, and 12.9% of the residents were considered low-income. Immigrants made up 17.6% of the population in 2000. Condominiums or flats accounted for 11.6% of the structures. While 18.4% of the stock was rented, the rest of the properties were occupied by their owners.</p>
            <p>The community's median age is 41.2 years, while the median age for the rest of Calgary is 37.4 years. Charleswood has an average of 2.5 persons per family and a near-equal gender ratio of 51% male and 49% female residents. Approximately 16% of the residents of Charleswood are above the age of 65, compared to 10% for the rest of Calgary.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Housing</h3>
            <p>The Charleswood community is tranquil, mature, and thriving. The development of this community started around 1959 and it's close to several prime amenities.</p>
            <p>The homes here have fantastic views, which is what draws many property seekers. There are largely single-family detached homes here that were constructed around 1960, however, there are also a few condominiums. Nose Hill Park, where Charleswood residences are located, is home to wonderful animals, natural grasslands, and old archaeological sites. This makes it a favourite location for nature and wildlife lovers.</p>
